  \hline
 & Mean \\ 
  \hline
Beautiful & 4.33 \\ 
  Average & 3.97 \\ 
  Unattractive & 5.81 \\ 
   \hline
\end{tabular}
\end{table}

If we use the {\tt diffmean} function from the {\tt mosaic} package, it will compute the difference in the group means for us. 

<<DiffMean>>=
require(mosaic)
diffmean(Years ~ Attr, data = MockJury, only.2 = FALSE)
@


We see that the mean sentence length for unattractive women is almost two years longer than for women of average attractiveness, while the sentence length for the beautiful women lies in the middle. There seems to be a big difference between the average and the unattractive groups, but we need statistics to decided whether this difference could be due to chance. Think back to 216. What are the two methods you learned to answer this question?

